ProMED Rapporteur Mahmoud Orabi

[[Avian influenza is still causing problems for poultry and backyard producers and hobby raisers. It seems late in the year to be seeing these cases. However, as fall migrations begin occurring, we are likely to see more cases. The hot summer was a bit of reprieve, but case numbers could increase again with the autumn migrations. So please keep your birds indoors and protected from other fowl. Keep your biosecurity in action. Protect your birds and yourselves. - Mod.TG

